shared_text:
Jason King
January 19 at 12:34 PM ·

Jaden’s first opponent in this weekend’s tournament was a young man with Down’s Syndrome. Once he saw who he was wrestling he knew what to do.

They exchanged takedowns and wrestled for 3 minutes. The smiles on the face of his opponent says it all! Everyone cheered for this young man so loudly...it was great!

When he came to shake my hand after the match I told him, “You did great on those takedowns you got!”
With an ear to ear grin on his face he beamed with joy and said “THANKS!!”

I know any one of our Celina Wrestlers would have done the same. Jaden was the fortunate one that got to represent his team and prove that a Champion is more than just a person who wins a match!

I love this sport!!!

(Music by Switchfoot. “Live It Well.”)

post_text:
Come out to the High School this Sunday at Noon to see the future of your NEW CRESTVIEW WRESTLING KNIGHTS!!!

WE DID IT!!!!

Tonight, Crestview approved the addition of Wrestling as a school sport!!!!

There are so many people to thank for this opportunity. This community has been so supportive of this program and we couldn’t have done it without that.

Coaches and more importantly, coaches wives are due a huge thanks for their commitment.

And, to all the kids that have taken on this opportunity and fallen in love with the sport. We can’t wait to see how this sport builds you as a person.

Also, thank you to the school administration that played such a big part in this. Mr. Bowen, Mr. Kreischer and Mrs. Mollenkopf. You all have been extremely helpful with this.

post_text:
This is one of the toughest kids you’ll ever meet. Reid Motycka wrestled his heart out yesterday. He was undefeated, pinning his first three opponents, winning his final match and on his way to sealing a team championship when he twisted his ankle and fractured his Tibia.

Reid didn’t even shed a tear through this. He ended the day in 2nd Place and we couldn’t be more proud of him!!

We hope you heal fast Reid and we can’t wait to see you continue to progress on the mat.

post_text:
The 2017/2018 season was amazing to be a part of! I believe we were the largest club every weekend that we competed! We turned a lot of heads and Convoy was a common discussion point everywhere that we went!!

Our kids hit milestones and improved tremendously throughout the season. Here are some of the team's stats/highlights:

Convoy was represented on the podium 154 times this season!!!!

29 individual championships were won!!!!

74 top two individual finishes were awarded!!!!

Wayne Trace Team Dual Champions!!!!

Fairview Tournament Champions!!!!

Wayne Trace and Antwerp Tournament 4th Place finishes!!!!

Honored at the OSU vs Iowa wrestling match!!!!

We also had a historic moment as we brought the first ever wrestling match inside the halls of Crestview!!!!

This was a fun year and I can't wait to do it again next year! Spread the word for next season! We have a lot of hidden talent walking our halls!!

post_text:
Wow! What a great night of wrestling tonight!! All of the kids did a fantastic job!! The talent in these Crestview kids is something to be proud of!!

I can't thank this community enough for the amazing show of support on our gun raffle!! It has been a blessing to start this club in this community and your support on this raffle will cover tournament costs for our kids throughout the season! Thank you so much!!

We'll be in action for the first time this season on Saturday at Liberty Center. These kids will be looking to bring home some team hardware and I think we've got the right group of kids to get that done. Action starts at 9 am if you want to see these kids compete.

We are kicking off our second annual gun raffle to help our kids pay for tournament costs. There are 500 tickets for 8 guns and are $20 a ticket. Message us here, stop in at the Convoy Community Building between 6-8 on Tuesdays and Thursdays or reach out to a parent from the club to get your tickets.

If all tickets are gone, we would like to hold a live drawing on January 2nd after our team scrimmage. Final details will be put out once tickets are sold.

Don't wait! These will go fast!
